</note>
<example id="fs-id2608792"><exercise id="fs-id1823280"><problem id="fs-id1627987">
<para id="fs-id2279010">Translate and solve: The difference of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>14</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>18</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id2477953">
<title>Solution</title>
<table id="eip-id1168469862237" class="unnumbered unstyled" summary="The image shows the sentence “The difference of y and 14 is 18.” Translate that to an algebraic equation to get y minus 14 equal to 18. Add 14 to both sides. The left side simplifies to y and the right is 18 plus 14 which is 32. The equation becomes y equal to 32. Substitute 32 back into the equation for y to check. Is 32 minus 14 equal to 18. Yes."><label/>
<tgroup cols="2"><colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="c2"/>
<colspec colnum="3" colname="c3"/>
<tbody>
  <row>
    <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2"/>
    <entry>The difference of <emphasis effect="italics">y</emphasis> and 14 is 18.</entry>
  </row>
  <row>
    <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2">Translate.</entry>
    <entry><media id="eip-id1168469872181" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_02_03_031_img-01.png"/></media></entry>
  </row>
  <row> 
    <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2">Add 14 to both sides.</entry>
    <entry><media id="eip-id1168469871413" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_02_03_031_img-02.png"/></media></entry>
  </row>
  <row>
    <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2">Simplify.</entry>
    <entry><media id="eip-id1168469876646" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_02_03_031_img-03.png"/></media></entry>
  </row>
  <row>
    <entry>We can check. Let <m:math><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:math>.</entry>
    <entry><media id="eip-id1168469868011" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_02_03_031_img-04.png"/></media></entry>
    <entry/>
  </row>
  <row>
    <entry/>
    <entry><media id="eip-id1168469877577" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_02_03_031_img-05.png"/></media></entry>
    <entry/>
  </row>
  <row>
    <entry/>
    <entry><media id="eip-id1168469877592" alt="."><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/CNX_BMath_Figure_02_03_031_img-06.png"/></media></entry>
    <entry/>
  </row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table><para id="fs-id1243266">So <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>32</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> is the solution.</para>
</solution>
</exercise></example><note id="fs-id2264886" class="try">
<exercise id="fs-id1919754">
<problem id="fs-id1863199">
<para id="fs-id1474925">Translate and solve:</para>
<para id="fs-id1300995">The difference of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mi>z</m:mi></m:mrow></m:math> and <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>17</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math> is equal to <m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>37</m:mn><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
</problem>
